  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-a9ed6e7990a7",
  "content": " overlap should carry heading context\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_name_and_extensions() {\n        let chunker = MarkdownChunker::new();\n        assert_eq!(chunker.name(), \"markdown\");\n        assert_eq!(chunker.supported_extensions(), &[\"md\"]);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Register module and run tests to verify they fail**\n\nAdd to `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`:\n```rust\npub mod chunking_markdown;\n```\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_markdown -- --nocapture`\nExpected: FAIL\n\n**Step 3: Implement MarkdownChunker**\n\nChunk algorithm:\n1. Scan lines for heading patterns (`^#{1,6} `)\n2. At each heading, emit the accumulated section as a chunk\n3. Content before the first heading (if any) gets its own chunk\n4. `chunk_type` = \"heading_section\" for headed chunks, \"text\" for pre-heading content\n\nOverride `overlap_context()` to extract heading hierarchy from the previous chunk (e.g., find the last `#` and `##` lines).\n\nOverride `merge_small()` to merge adjacent sections at the same heading level under the same parent heading.\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_markdown -- --nocapture`\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_markdown.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.3): MarkdownChunker — heading-based section splitting (D68)\"\n```\n\n---\n",
